The paper deals with a distributed source coding problem with distortion constraints, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The source vectors are Gaussian, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM), where Gaussian models are commonly used. The paper also considers the presence of side information at the decoder, which is a topic in signal processing and information theory (cs.SI). The problem involves encoding a sequence of observations, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), where sequence processing is a common topic. Finally, the paper derives lower and upper bounds on the rate-distortion function, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
